
<div class="container" style="margin-top:2%;">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col">
      <div class='text-center'>
        <%= image_tag("EHR-Predict_Logo 2.png", :class => 'mx-auto w-75 h-75')%>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="col">
      <div class='text-center mt-5'>
        <h1>EHR Predict</h1>
        <h5 class='text-muted'>The premiere mortality predictive tool at Texas A&M University</h5>
      </div>
      
      <div class='text-center mt-5'>
        <div class='card'>
            <div class='card-header text-center' style="background:#2b2a2d; color:#fff">
                <h5>Please upload a CSV in the standardized file format</h5>
            </div>
            <div class='card-body'>
                <%= render 'form' %>
            </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
  </div>
  
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col">
      <div class="progress">
        <div class="progress-bar bg-primary" role="progressbar" style="width: 100%" aria-valuenow="100" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100"></div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="mx-auto mt-2" style="width:85%">
        <h5 class='text-muted'>EHR Predict is a mortality predictive tool which utilizes Machine Learning to predict the likelihood of a 
        given patient dying within a 24 hour period. The system takes in a timeseries data sheet and uses, primarlily, the following variables
        to make its prediction:</h5>
        
        <hr>
        
        <div class="row mt-1">
          <div class="col">
            <h5 class="text-muted">
              <ul>
                <li>Demographic Information</li>
                <li>Heart Rate</li>
                <li>Heart Rhythm</li>
                <li>Blood Pressure</li>
                <li>GCS Total</li>
                <li>Platelet Count</li>
                <li>Creatinine</li>
              </ul>
            </h5>
          </div>
          <div class="col">
            <h5 class="text-muted">The EHR Predict system utilizes a custom model generated from cleaed data pulled from the 
            <a href="https://mimic.physionet.org/" target="_blank">MIMIC Critical Care Database</a>. EHR Predict has been found to have a 
            <strong>ROC score of 0.86</strong> which is significantly higher than the common metric for success of 0.75.</h5>
          </div>
          
      </div>
    </div>
    
  </div>
</div>